TITLE: GOP questions Trump subpoena timing: 'Made-for-TV prop'
SUMMARY: It's highly unlikely former President Donald Trump will testify before the Jan. 6 Committee, raising questions about why it waited so long to subpoena him.

TITLE: Wisconsin Senate debate: Crowd erupts as Johnson, Barnes asked to say something nice about each other
SUMMARY: Sen. Ron Johnson was booed Thursday night after turning a question about what he finds admirable in opponent Lt. Gov. Mandela Barnes into a criticism.

TITLE: North Carolina Dem who says she supports law enforcement endorsed by far-left defund police group
SUMMARY: A radical anti-police group endorsed Cheri Beasley, the Democratic Senate candidate in North Carolina, in part because of her support for reforming the criminal justice system.

TITLE: Was Stacey Abrams' 2018 election stolen? Voters in Georgia refuse to give up on debunked claim
SUMMARY: Voters in South Fulton, Georgia, largely supported Stacey Abrams' claim that the 2018 gubernatorial election was stolen from her, though they were non-committal.

TITLE: Kamala Harris ducks Latin America despite assignment to discover the 'root causes' of illegal immigration
SUMMARY: Vice President Kamala Harris has spent only three days over the course of two trips to Latin America since she took office as border encounters hit an all-time high.

TITLE: WATCH: Democratic Sen. Raphael Warnock dodges question on abortion limitations
SUMMARY: Sen. Raphael Warnock, D-Ga., dodged a question from Fox News Digital about abortion limitations, and said Democrats should forge ahead with its focus on abortion ahead of the midterms.

TITLE: New video shows Pelosi threatened to 'punch out' Trump on Jan. 6: 'I’m going to go to jail'
SUMMARY: House Speaker Nancy Pelosi threatened to punch then-President Trump in a newly shown video from January 6, 2021. In the video, Pelosi says she would "punch him out."

TITLE: FBI paid Igor Danchenko more than $200,000 to serve as confidential human source
SUMMARY: The FBI paid Russian national Igor Danchenko more than $200,000 to serve as a confidential human source from 2017 to late 2020.

TITLE: FBI agent testifies that losing Danchenko as human source harms US national security
SUMMARY: An FBI agent testified Thursday that Igor Danchenko was a valuable FBI informant and said losing him as a covert human source harms U.S. national security.

TITLE: Sen. Patrick Leahy taken to hospital in Washington 'as a precaution' after not feeling well
SUMMARY: Sen. Patrick Leahy, D-Vt., the longest-serving member of the U.S. Senate, was hospitalized "as a precaution" on Thursday, his office said.

TITLE: Virginia state lawmaker to introduce bill making it a crime for parents not to affirm their LGBT child
SUMMARY: A Virginia state delegate said she will introduce a bill that would make it a crime for a parent not to affirm their child's sexual orientation or gender identity.

TITLE: Two swing House seats in spotlight in battleground of Nevada
SUMMARY: Two out of four of Nevada's U.S. House races are swing-seats as Republicans attempt to win in a state that Donald Trump failed to carry in 2016.

TITLE: ACLU, legal groups suing Biden admin for denying legal representation to detained migrants
SUMMARY: The American Civil Liberties Union filed a lawsuit against Immigration and Customs Enforcement on Thursday alleging that detained migrants have been denied legal representation.

TITLE: Top 5 moments from latest Jan. 6 hearing before midterm elections include Trump subpoena, new video
SUMMARY: The House select committee investigating the Jan. 6, 2021, assault on the U.S. Capitol concluded its latest hearing, likely the final meeting before the midterm elections.

TITLE: Mayorkas 'whipgate' bombshell likely to worsen relations between DHS secretary, border agents
SUMMARY: New revelations over false allegations that Border Patrol agents "whipped" migrants are likely to worsen relations between agents and Secretary Alejandro Mayorkas.

TITLE: Trump 'loves the idea of testifying' before Jan. 6 committee: source close to the former president
SUMMARY: EXCLUSIVE: Former President Donald Trump “loves the idea of testifying” before the House select committee investigating January 6th, a source close to Trump told Fox News Digital just after the panel unanimously voted to subpoena him.

TITLE: Dem running in tight race vows to vote for Nancy Pelosi, 'but then after that, it’s my district'
SUMMARY: Democratic Rep. Henry Cuellar of Texas said that his "first vote is for Nancy Pelosi" if he wins his congressional election in November, despite criticizing Democrats' border policies.

TITLE: Former President Donald Trump subpoenaed by January 6 Committee
SUMMARY: The House select committee investigating the Jan. 6, 2021, riot at the U.S. Capitol voted unanimously to subpoena former President Donald Trump to testify.

TITLE: Democrat candidate accused of 'whitewashing' Hispanic GOP opponent in new ad
SUMMARY: Alexis Martinez Johnson, a Hispanic Republican running to represent New Mexico's 3rd Congressional District in the House, has accused Democratic challenger Rep. Teresa Leger Fernandez of "whitewashing" her name in a recent campaign ad.

TITLE: CT Gov. Lamont's office violated open records laws in AP case
SUMMARY: According to the Connecticut Freedom of Information Commission, Gov. Ned Lamont's office violated the open records laws after they took two years to file documents related to COVID.
